<!-- 

Review page for singles, where we sent the single information that is being reviewed,
we list the single name next to a review for: so the user knows what they're reviewing.

reviewSingle holds the content of the query that got the information of the single, and name
is the attribute holding the single name.

the hidden select values are so we can easily pass values to ourselves in the post requests. values such 
as the singleid or the single name

--> 

<form class="pure-u-4-5 pure-form" style="width:80%; padding-left:18% " method="post" action="/post_as">
    <fieldset class="pure-g">
        <legend class="pure-u-1" style="color: white; background-color: black; text-align:center; font-size:2em;">
            {{#each reviewSingle}}

            Review For: {{name}}</legend>
        <select style='display:none;' name='single_id'>
            <option value="{{ singleid }}" selected>{{ singleid }}</option>
        </select>


<!-- 

Textarea here is just a text box where the user can write all that they want, once it's submitted, it's instantly updated on the database
to show what they wrote, what they wrote it about, and when it was submitted.

-->
       
        <textarea name="review" rows="4" cols="100" style="color: black; width:100%;" placeholder="Say something about {{name}}..."></textarea>
        {{/each}}
        <input id="review" class="pure-u-1-5 pure-button pure-button-primary" type="submit" value="Post"/>
        <button formaction="/likedAlbum" class="fa fa-thumbs-up green_button counter-btn" style="font-size:48px">
            Like </button>
    </fieldset>
</form>
